{
  "stem": "20616.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they-- they all say, oh, I was against Hitler.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the reason they gave is not what he did, but that he started something that he didn't finish, the misery that he-- that the German people received when the cities were bombed and the people were killed and the soldiers didn't come back and the wounded were just starting to trickle back and the-- a lot of them was still in the Russian-- captured by the Russians, some of them were walking in horrible conditions and arriving.",
      "word_count": 78
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the first Jewish refugees came out of the concentration camps and some of them settled here in Neustadt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was a very unpleasant and unhappy situation which took place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Of course, we tried to help them as much as we could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were like skeletons.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We fed them, we gave them all the food that we could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we also put them into a winery where they would run the-- bottling wine and selling it and distributing it-- that belonged to a Nazi who had fled.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they were very grateful that they could do that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But their attitude was such they-- all of a sudden we got reports that they watered the wine and they did all kinds of things.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And when we confronted them, their rationale was after what the Germans did to us, we don't have any scruples treating them any way we can and taking advantage of them any way we can.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So we tried to instill them that they were supposed to be-- that we put them-- put them in there to act as models-- and as-- as role models more than anything else.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They could not understand that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we had to-- that was one of the saddest jobs that-- that I had.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
